quote:
Originally posted by kiya
Tannith was also good as a Goa'uld. They always use British actors or American actors speaking with English accents to play bad guys and I've always thought that it's really quite effective. What is it about the English accent? Why does it sound so menacing?
The world sees Americans and Canadians as somewhat naieve in comparison to the stalwart and gentlemanly Brits. The British have an awful lot more heraldic history than the Americans (a rather young nation by comparison). Furthermore, the British accent is usually delivered well in such a manner as to inspire an air of authority without needing to back it up with action. Oh, and it is usually delivered without any "degradation" of the language. Someone who makes good use of language is someone very careful, perhaps cunning. Hmm, lost my train of thought...
